The&nbsp;Kisumu&nbsp;MCA&nbsp;who disappeared on Thursday evening has&nbsp;resurfaced, saying his life is still in danger. Mr Paul Okwiri of West&nbsp;Kisumu&nbsp;ward&nbsp;resurfaced&nbsp;unharmed in Rongo town, Migori County, about 150km from&nbsp;Kisumu town, at 9pm on Friday, nearly 12 hours since he went missing. Police in Rongo questioned him then handed him over to their colleagues in Maseno,&nbsp;Kisumu&nbsp;County, for further interrogation. Okwiri said he was abducted by three men and a woman as he drove to his home on Thursday night. They blindfolded him and drove to an unknown destination, with the woman behind the wheels, he said. Stance against corruption He said he still feared for his life because of his stance against corruption. READ MORE Three police cars set ablaze in Dresden ahead of German Unity Day celebrations Kisumu MCA found after kidnap says he had told police his life was in danger Stolen day-old baby found alive and hidden in house Okwiri narrated that he was driving to his home in Sinyolo village at 11pm on Thursday, when three people emerged from a nearby banana plantation. &ldquo;They bundled me into the car boot, after which they blindfolded me and drove for long. They took me to a small room where they hid me overnight,&rdquo; he said. He said the kidnappers asked him how much money he had accumulated for the 2017 election campaigns and told him to forego his ambition of being re-elected or they would kill him. Okwiri was found by boda boda operators at Nyarach Junction, about two kilometres from Rongo town on Friday night. &ldquo;He was found in a state of confusion and the riders brought him to the police station,&rdquo; said Rongo OCPD Kisaka Muganda. The&nbsp;MCA&nbsp;was in a grey long-sleeved T-shirt, a brown pair of trousers and a pair of slippers. GO TO PAGE 1 2 Next &raquo;